    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> What is the advantage of using this contract based testing approach as opposed to one which is inspecting `geth` directly?\r\n\r\nWhen we originally scoped this out it felt simpler to have the contract store the relevant metrics that we want to keep track of vs doing a O(n) search through all the blocks to detect anomalies. I'm personally not opinionated about which is better & would lean towards whatever is easier.\r\n\r\nOne benefit of doing the integrity checks on Geth's entire blockchain (not using the contract) is that it might be easier to slot in the monotonicity checks as well. Might end up being a more flexible approach though I think also depends on the overall architecture of the load tests. I'll add this as an alternative solution.",
